Sixty-ninth
Legislative Assembly SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 4029
of North Dakota
Introduced by
Senators Magrum, Van Oosting
Representatives Holle, S. Olson
1 A concurrent resolution directing the Legislative Management to consider studying the costs
2 and effects of planting and tending to sterile monoculture invasive plants and native plants
3 within the state.
4 WHEREAS, North Dakota has a diverse range of grasses and plants within the state; and
5 WHEREAS, many plants and grasses are native to the state, while other plants and
6 grasses have been transported and planted from other parts of the region, country, and world;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, the Legislative Assembly should assess whether foreign or native plants and
9 grasses, or a combination of both, best promote the various ecosystems of our state;
10 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF NORTH DAKOTA, THE
11 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING THEREIN:
12 That the Legislative Management shall consider studying the cost of planting sterile
13 monoculture invasive plants as opposed to native prairie plants throughout the state; and
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the study must include a comparison of mowing,
15 seeding, and herbicide and pesticide application practices and other costs and effects
16 associated with planting each type of plant in the state; and
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the study must include an analysis of how monoculture
18 invasive plants and native prairie plants affect the various ecosystems of the state; and
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislative Management report its findings and
20 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
21 the Seventieth Legislative Assembly.
